wiki.summary: "Señorita" (English: "Young Lady") is a song by Canadian singer Shawn Mendes and Cuban-American singer Camila Cabello. It was released as a single through Island Records on June 21, 2019. The song was written by Mendes, Cabello, Charli XCX, Ali Tamposi, Jack Patterson of Clean Bandit, and its producers Andrew Watt, Benny Blanco, and Cashmere Cat. The song marks Mendes' and Cabello's second collaboration, following "I Know What You Did Last Summer", a song from Mendes' debut album, Handwritten (2015). Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Señorita" (English: "Young Lady") is a song by Canadian singer Shawn Mendes and Cuban-American singer Camila Cabello. It was released as a single through Island Records on June 21, 2019. The song was written by Mendes, Cabello, Charli XCX, Ali Tamposi, Jack Patterson of Clean Bandit, and its producers Andrew Watt, Benny Blanco, and Cashmere Cat. The song marks Mendes' and Cabello's second collaboration, following "I Know What You Did Last Summer", a song from Mendes' debut album, Handwritten (2015). "Señorita" topped the charts in Austria, Bulgaria, the Czech Republic, Denmark, Finland, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Ireland, Malaysia, the Netherlands, New Zealand, Norway, Portugal, Singapore, Slovakia, Sweden, Switzerland and the United Kingdom, and reached number two in Australia, Canada, Estonia and the United States. It also went on to record the biggest single-day debut of a male/female duet ever. Read more on Last.fm.
